T1  - Optimal Dynamic Information Acquisition
AU  - Zhong, Weijie
Y1  - 2022/07/01
PY  - 2022
DA  - 2022/07/01
DO  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA17787
T2  - Econometrica
JF  - Econometrica
JO  - Econometrica
JA  - Econometrica
SP  - 1537
EP  - 1582
VL  - 90
IS  - 4
KW  - Dynamic information acquisition
KW  - rational inattention
KW  - Poisson process
PB  - John Wiley & Sons, Ltd
SN  - 0012-9682
UR  - https://doi.org/10.3982/ECTA17787
Y2  - 2024/03/26
N2  - I study a dynamic model in which a decision-maker (DM) acquires information about the payoffs of different alternatives prior to making a decision. The model's key feature is the flexibility of information: the DM can choose any dynamic signal process as an information source, subject to a flow cost that depends on the informativeness of the signal. Under the optimal policy, the DM acquires a signal that arrives according to a Poisson process. The optimal Poisson signal confirms the DM's prior belief and is sufficiently precise to warrant immediate action. Over time, given the absence of the arrival of a Poisson signal, the DM continues seeking an increasingly precise but less frequent Poisson signal.
ER  - 

